  publisher    = {ACM},
  note         = {Proposes \emph{AI-oriented grammar} — programming-language design optimised for LLM consumption rather than human readability. Introduces \emph{SimPy}, a Python variant with formatting/whitespace tokens stripped while preserving identical AST. Empirical: -13.5\% tokens on CodeLlama, -10.4\% on GPT-4, with maintained or improved task performance. Bidirectional Python ↔ SimPy transformation. Most direct prior art for the LLM-prompting-density hypothesis in 05 §6 — surfaced 2026-05-12 in the open-items lit pass. Approach is different from Inflexión's (Sun et al. strip formatting; Inflexión engages natural-language morphological density), but both occupy the same emerging design space: LLM-oriented PL design. CONFIRM exact venue/proceedings details before publication.},
  keywords     = {lengua, babel}
}

